SYMPTOM_TEXT: RN stated the client stood up quickly after receiving the vaccine and was standing next to his mother while his sister was receiving the COVID vaccine. Client reported feeling nauseous to his mother and the client's mother alerted RN. RN provided a chair for the client. The client removed his mask and RN noted sweat on the client's face. The client was offered water and took a small sip. RN and Ancillary were fanning the client. RN  entered the vaccination room, noted RN fanning the client, and responded. RN offered the client juice and the client took a few sips. The client reported nausea to RN . Vitals were obtained with a pulse oximeter at 2:20PM and were as follows: HR 77, O2 99. The client began vomiting into an emesis bag at 2:21PM. After emesis, the client stated he felt better. RN began obtaining a blood pressure reading around 2:24PM, the reading was difficult for RN to hear but was approximately 82/60. EMT responded. RN noted new onset of pallor of the client's lips and face. The client was provided a cotton ball with peppermint oil on it to smell. The client stood up with assistance and transferred into an antigravity chair. The chair was reclined to a semi-fowler's position. The client denied any persistent nausea. At 2:28PM vitals obtained with the pulse oximeter were as follows: HR 78, O2 99%. BP obtained at 2:31PM was 86/60. The client's mother stated the client did not have any current medications, chronic conditions, or known allergies. The client ate at a fast food chain prior to coming to the vaccination site. The client's mother denied any history of syncope or nausea with vaccinations. The client reported a history of nausea when riding in the car. RN noted return of reddish color to the client's lips and face. Respirations were 24 per minute at 2:33PM. At 2:36PM the client stated he felt normal. Vitals obtained at 2:36PM were as follows: BP 98/72, HR 92, O2 99%, RR 18. RN provided education to the client and his mother regarding s/s of anaphylaxis and when to seek EMS. RN recommended the client's mother follow up with the client's primary care provider within 24 hours regarding the client's symptoms. The client and the client's mother voiced understanding of this education. The anti-gravity chair was adjusted to a high folwer's position. Vitals obtained at 2:46PM were as follows: O2 99%, HR 90, BP 98/68. The client stated he felt normal. The client's mother confirmed that the current state was normal for the client. The client stood up unassisted from the anti-gravity chair. At 2:50 PM the client ambulated from the vaccination room to the observation area with a steady gait while holding his mom's hand. The client ambulated unassisted with a steady gait out of the vaccination site at 3:04PM.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After I went to bed on Nov 24th, I noticed I was very itchy and my right leg ached. I was vaguely remembered something like that happening about a week after my first or second Moderna shot so I didn't think much of it. However on the 25th the itchiness continued. Eventually it became severe enough that I looked in the a mirror and was shocked at how red my skin was. The rash seemed to move around my body, coming and going. By evening it wasn't just red but raised welts and painful. I could even feel welts in my ear canals. The skin on the back of my head and neck felt weird and stiff.  I went to urgent care the next day. The provider there didn't know what caused it and did not believe it is related to the vaccine, and gave me a steroid shot and prescriptions for oral steroids and antihistamines. By that evening the itchiness has spread to the palms of my hands and bottoms of my feet. However the sensation was less painful and itchy and I was able to sleep.  The next day I didn't feel itchy, however my skin was very prone to getting red where touched. This continued even after I ran out of steroids after 10 days. I saw a dermatologist who was convinced it was from the vaccine, doesn't want me to get any more covid shots, and urged me to see an allergist. I will be seeing an allergist on 12/20/21. In preparation for this I stopped taking the antihistamine on 12/13 and the itching has become quite severe again but the welts are not as bad.
CUR_ILL: Diagnoses with strep (not tested for it though.)

Tinnitus-High pitched humming/whistle that started after about 48 hours after vaccine. Able to cover ears and thump lower back of head at same time with fingers to relax muscle (dentist recommended online). After doing maneuver intermittently over few hours it would go away, but come back over time. I'm a nurse and looked up and saw it was a possible side affect and most went away after 2 weeks. It continued to come and go and would cause migraine when it continued for long periods. Tylenol and IBU didnt help so had to keep ice pack on head to get some relief.  At first could drown out with alarms noise and people at work and with TV at home to sleep. Length of time it continued without a break got worst with time. Now it's been a month and it seems to be getting worst. Will see Dr soon as possible knowing there's nothing for them to do unfortunately.  I don't know if this is permanent or there's still time for it to go away only time will tell.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Period started 16 days early with none of my usual PMS symptoms and was unusually painful and heavy

About 2 to 4 weeks, some persistent shoulder pain started, and kept steady for the following months. It was bothersome especially when trying to sleep on the should, but occasionally also some movements. After taking a third dose in mid November 2021 (Moderna), and after the acute pain of the shot passed (3 days), the previous persistent pain became a lot worse, and now hurts with almost every movement and seems to be getting worse every week. I will soon do more tests.
LAB_DATA: The tests (MRI) showed 2 partially torn tendons. I believe that is probably not caused by the vaccine, but I am sure there is some other source of pain, other than the tendons, in my shoulder, not sure if muscular or neurological. Some movements that should hurt with tendon injuries don't, and others that shouldn't do. Also the fact that it got significantly worse after the 3rd shot clearly indicates to me that this is vaccine related. It is already impacting my quality of life, and if this keeps getting worse I don't know what will be. I plan on repeating the MRIs soon and also talking to a neurologist.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My tinnitus got worse after the second shot.  The ringing in my ears got worse. The increase ringing in my years started a fews days after my second dose of the Moderna vaccine.  I went to the Ear Nose and Throat doctor in July or Early August of 2021. The doctor cleaned my ears to remove ear wax. I was also given a hearing test. My hearing was normal.  I also notice that when I drive on the interstate or a road where the speed limit is 55 or greater my tinnitus gets louder. This can also happen when I drive to the store or make short trips.   So basically my tinnitus is now is louder and very much unpredictable.  Since driving is now effecting my tinnitus I am now seeking a medical accommodation from the Administration to work from home so that I do not have to drive to work. I have a medical disability from the Administration.  This was obtain in 2016.  Also after the second dose my throat was dry. It was difficult to swallow. I had to drink a lot of water. I had to eat soup and soft foods for a few weeks. I also got constipated. The constipation lasted a few days.
LAB_DATA: The Ear Nose and Throat doctor performed a hearing test. My hearing was normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Before having my 2nd shot on the 17/12/21, I advised the nurse that after my first shot my heart started a little weird arythmia after 5 minutes of receiving the vaccine, that one week after the vaccine I had to stop exercising as my heart was jumping all over the place.   She advised I should wait a few minutes before going out to the waiting room  to see how I was.  Within 1 minute of receiving the vaccine, I felt my heart racing.  I started to feel light headed and was told to lie down by the nurse.  My heart continued to race, the nurse checked my blood pressure 3 times.  I started getting tingling in my legs and arms and within 10 minutes quite sore up my left arm.  My head was so light headed, I thought I would never be able to stand up again I felt so bad.  The ambulance was called.  I was taken into the ambulance where they did a thorough ECG.  Everything was fine after an hour.  I couldnt drive.  The rest of the day was uneasy breathing.  The next day had aches and pains.  Took panadol.. Little palpatations have begun daily since Saturday.  My arm is still sore, red, swollen and itchy.  Very different to my first vaccine.  Have done all the icing regularly etc. But feels odd.

PRIOR_VAX: Moderna COVID Vaccine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 36 hours after my dose, or the 2nd night, I woke up at 6am with a racing heartbeat of 90-100 beats per minute.  My normal sleeping heart rate is in the mid to high 40's, or low 50's. I had no idea why my heart was racing at 90-100 beats per minute but I quickly realized there was something wrong.   Waiting at the hospital waiting room it was consistenly around 83 bpm, very high from my normal resting heart rate of 53.   I also had some vague chest tightness but only for a few moments, and a vague pain, again, only for a few moments.  Mostly very rapid heart rate that lasted for HOURS.  and a lot of shortness of breath.  They did tests for some hours and could not find anything officially heart-wise and as I was laying there trying to relax my heart rate came down slightly, into the 70's and touching 69 I was lay still and as relaxed as I could, so they discharged me.  Back in the car my bpm was back in the 80's as I was no longer laying down and while driving home back to 100ish, but I felt a bit better knowing I wasn't having a life threatening issue in the moment.   I was fortunately able to sleep, making sure to keep my arm at my side in bed and not putting even 1 bit of pressure on my chest, and not sleeping on my side or my chest, as I slept on my side that night of the problem and that is when my heart started fluttering I believe.   So if I lay in bed on my back and lay completley still, I have been able to sleep and not feel wierd chest feelings as I normally might.  But the scariest part now is the extreme shortness of breath.  The first day after (day 3 from shot - Thursday, shot was Monday at 4:30pm) I could barely go 5 steps without being completely winded.  I could barely go up or down stairs, or do much of anything.  Each day I get just slightly..better...as now on day 5 I can go up the stairs in only 1 minute...instead of 2.  I still have to go step by step and it feels like I am climbing a mountain and then am very tired and must rest.  I am hoping I continue to get better but I am very concerned if this will have any long term health effects for me, as that is the entire reason why I avoided covid to such a great degree, as I knew I had some kind of allergic asthmya like condition perhaps, but not officially asthyma (that I know of.)    Presently now Sunday night day 6, my heart rate is often in the 70's although when sleeping and resting it does go down to mid 40's during sleep and 50s sometimes when still.  but other times sitting still it can be 70's or 80's which is abnormal and my ox level often goes to down to 93, while I am sitting and doing no movement.  It also often says 96 or 97, again while doing...nothing. and being still.   While walking just a few steps it went down to 89 on the first or 2nd day.  I have not exerted myself much as I cannot much, and out of fear of creating another problem, or something worse.       I was givin no treatment and they told me I had "stress", which clearly I do not, I was as relaxed as possible which thankfully brought the bpm down to 69/70's range, but for me that is still much elevated and I knew something was not right, but I understood that they likely could not find anything and it was getting busier and they likely had to fill the beds with others.    I am on day 6 and this feels like it could last likely weeks, or months, again, I have been given no medication and have no diagnosis and medical professionals and been of very little help, besides doing some tests and watching me during the intial heart rate issue.   This issue must be studied much more to understand what is happening and it is unnaceptable that not enough people know these risks.
LAB_DATA: They did EKG, T test and chest x-ray, I was told nothing specific found, which I read also happened to someone else, who later nearly died of it, and had to have his chest opened up in surgery. I have not gone back to the hospital since the initial scare, so I haven't had any follow ups done and my visit with the cardiologist is not until mid January, where I hope to the get the MRI, for a diagnosis.
OTHER_MEDS: Escitalopram 10mg per day. (anti-depressant, anti anxiety); I also take GNC performance and vitality supplement, 1/2 recommended dose, so 1 pill per day. Fish Oil. Gingko Biloba. Flaxseed Oil. "calm cleanse" by nature's bounty or other bra
CUR_ILL: None that I know of. I do have costochondritis history and it is normal for me to have some minor pain around my heart and chest as I rest my hand while holding my phone while I read in bed, probably about 1 hour + per day. I was concerned about the costochondritis and the Moderna vaccine, but as I took the Pfizer 2x, and had no problem, and Moderna was providing better protection, I figured I would probably be OK to get that. Way wrong decision and now that I see how dangerous the Moderna vax is, it is very, very concerning. This data was not made well known to me how only every 1 in 23,000 locally got it from Moderna so our media has not done a good job giving this information, and I hope I can sue in 2024, as it is ridiculous to keep telling people these vaccines are safe when people are dying from them routinely. Especially if one has a condition like costochondritis, but was not listed on the questionnaire as a possible problem. Horrible.
HISTORY: I have a history of depression, anxiety, panic attacks, social anxiety, and at one time agoraphobia. I spent 2 years in a dorm room by myself in college, but later recovered from most of those issues with therapy and medication. So for the last many years I just take 1/2 of my escitalopram dose, and I am mentally quite healthy. As mentioned - the costochondritis - so I thought I was maybe having a heart attack a few years ago and went to the hospital but was diagnosed as costochondritis (I was helping with my sick mom, lifting her a lot, and apparently that repeated movement led to the sharper or more concerning muscle spasm near my heart I was feeling). I routinely feel occasional odd feelings, it feels like almost like little bruising over my chest plate and heart area from putting weight down as I hold my phone, and then sleep on it. I also routinely have a pain in that same spot under my heart, when I am in a rush and bend over to tie my shoes before leaving, I think lack of oxygen to that spot perhaps, and it gets very sore, just in the spot, for about 5-10 seconds as I bend over a bit out of breath. Right under my heart in the same spot I had the scary spasms that time. So I routinely have some odd symptoms, whether costo or some other condition, I do not know, but that was the diagnoses I was given at that time.
ALLERGIES: Sometimes I wake up and my tonsil or thing that hangs from your throat. Every few months I wake up and it is swollen and can get hard to breathe. It gets inflamed and enlarges to the point that it interferes with my airway sometimes and sits on my tongue. It seems to possibly happen when my room or basement is very dusty. Also when cleaning and exposed so some old mold stuff in a dirty basement. So I don't know what I am allergic to, but I seem to have a strange allergic reaction, especially if my room window is closed and the room is too dusty, (this is why I stayed indoors for nearly 2 years...trying NOT to get Covid and now I have Covid like symptoms and likely myocarditis from the vaccine).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: It feels just like the time I had fluid around my heart. I think that's what this is; I'm having massive pain in my joints; Nausea; I'm thinking I had a heart attack; I felt like I can't catch my breath; Constant pain in my chest/I'm having constant pain in my chest.; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of CHEST PAIN (Constant pain in my chest/I'm having constant pain in my chest.), FEELING ABNORMAL (It feels just like the time I had fluid around my heart. I think that's what this is), MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION (I'm thinking I had a heart attack) and DYSPNOEA (I felt like I can't catch my breath) in a male patient of an unknown age who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     The patient's past medical history included Heart attack (had a heart attack 2 yrs ago) and Pericarditis (Pericarditis about 10 to 12 yrs ago.).    In November 2021, the patient received third dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) 1 dosage form. On 03-Dec-2021, the patient experienced CHEST PAIN (Constant pain in my chest/I'm having constant pain in my chest.) (seriousness criterion medically significant), MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION (I'm thinking I had a heart attack) (seriousness criterion medically significant), DYSPNOEA (I felt like I can't catch my breath) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and NAUSEA (Nausea). On 08-Dec-2021, the patient experienced FEELING ABNORMAL (It feels just like the time I had fluid around my heart. I think that's what this is) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and ARTHRALGIA (I'm having massive pain in my joints). At the time of the report, CHEST PAIN (Constant pain in my chest/I'm having constant pain in my chest.), FEELING ABNORMAL (It feels just like the time I had fluid around my heart. I think that's what this is), MYOCARDIAL INFARCTION (I'm thinking I had a heart attack), DYSPNOEA (I felt like I can't catch my breath), ARTHRALGIA (I'm having massive pain in my joints) and NAUSEA (Nausea) outcome was unknown.            Patient had a heart attack 2 years ago and  Pericarditis  10 to 12 years ago. Concomitant medications were not reported.  Patient had Moderna Covid-19 vaccine booster dose on 28Nov2021 or 29Nov2021 . On 03Dec 2021, Patient thought he had heart attack, he had nausea, constant pain in his chest and felt like he could not catch his breath. On 08 Dec 2021, patient felt like the time he had fluid around my heart, he reported having massive pain in his joints and constant pain in his chest.  I really don't want to go to the doctor. I just don't want to start racking up huge hospital bills. No treatment information was provided by the reporter.   Company comment: This spontaneous case concerns a male patient of unknown age with a relevant medical history of Myocardial infarction and Pericarditis, who experienced the  unexpected serious (medically significant) events of Chest pain, Dyspnoea and suspected Myocardial infarction and the expected serious (medically significant) event of suspected Pericarditis after mRNA- 1273 Moderna vaccine. The onset of the events occurred approximately 4 days after the booster dose of mRNA- 1273 vaccine. Clinical manifestations included nausea, chest pain, dyspnoea and subsequently the patient also developed Arthralgia. Initially, the patient thought he was having a heart attack, but he later on suspected Pericarditis. However, medical consultation we not performed. Prior history of Myocardial infarction and Pericarditis remain a confounder. The benefit-risk relationship of mRNA- 1273 vaccine is not affected by this report.; Sender's Comments: Company comment: This spontaneous case concerns a male patient of unknown age with a relevant medical history of Myocardial infarction and Pericarditis, who experienced the  unexpected serious (medically significant) events of Chest pain, Dyspnoea and suspected Myocardial infarction and the expected serious (medically significant) event of suspected Pericarditis after mRNA- 1273 Moderna vaccine. I still have pain off and on, and noticed that my heart races from time to time.

Got an IV of Benadryl and steroids, and they urged me to get an appt with an allergist since we didn't know what had caused my reaction.  By Friday I was still breaking out. 80-year-old male presents emergency department by EMS in no acute distress with stable vital signs. He is not hypoxic.  5 days ago he was seen with his wife in the emergency department and both diagnosed with Covid. She was hypoxic and he was not so she was admitted and he went home. He has been on steroids.  He called EMS tonight because he still did not feel good, he was weak and he vomited twice.  No chest pain.  No fever.  His blood sugar was over 400.  He states he was a borderline diabetic.  His blood sugar in the hospital 5 days ago was 249.  He does not take any diabetic medication including orals or insulin. Associated Symptoms: cough, fatigue, nausea, URI symptoms, vomiting, weakness
LAB_DATA: Cardiac work-up was ordered. His blood sugar read "high" on the last check by paramedics. EKG shows a sinus rhythm with no acute ischemic changes. There is a right bundle branch block that was present on his previous visit. No ectopy. Chest x-ray is negative. Patient's labs are reviewed. His blood sugar was 911. Creatinine appears to be stable at 1.7. Calcium is 4.8. Patient will be started on an insulin drip at 5 units/h. He is in the process of getting a liter bolus and after that will be run 125 of normal saline. 20 mEq of potassium will be added to that liter bag and he will get that over 8 hours. Every hour glucose will be done. The patient will be admitted to the ICU.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: First was extreme pressure on upper chest, gland and head.  Went to Urgent Care.  Was give a Z-pack for sinus infection,  was tested for Covid since I had many of the same symptons.  Was given the short test and long.  Both were negative.  Started feeling a little better but then it seemed to moving into pneumonia.  I had drainage and chest was hurting  My doctor put me on 10 days of Cefdinir 300 mg.  On 3//31/2021 called Doctor and told him I was not getting better.  He ordered a chest X-ray to be done the next morning.  I woke up that morning and got extremely dizzy and nauseated and passed out and hit my marble floor.  I moved to another room and preceeded to pass ouout again.  I was driven to the Emergency room that morning April 1, 2021.  I had heart rate spiking and all different rhythms, afib, fluttering etc.  All things that had never happened to me before.   I ended up in the hospital for a week(got out on April 7) after begging to go home.  I seemed to be getting worse at the hospital  I had every type of test they could give me and lots of bloodwork.   My CRP was 159.  They swabbed me for every infectious disease they could.  All came back negative.  I had Pericarditis, fluid in my lungs and many heart issues with rate and rhythms.  When I was released I was on many medications, I was on Sotalol 80 mg, Diltiazem 60 mg, Olmesartan Medoxomil 40 mg, Ibuprofen 600 mg, Colchicine .6 mg. and Xarelto.     I was very sick for all of April and most of  May.  I had bloodwork taken and white count was going up and my CRP went back up to 126.  I went to a Pullmonologist.  I had all the Covid symptom for those 2 months.  I ran fevers constantly, had terrible night sweat along with everything else.  Finally I was sent to a Rheumotologist on May 18, 2021.  I was still very sick with fevers and all the symptoms mentioned above.  He took 13 vials of blood and immediately put me on Chloroquine 250 mg/once a day.  My CRP was 126 at the time.   Two days after taking the Chloroquine I woke up and felt like I could actually take a deep breath.  At that point I felt like maybe I would get better.  After being on Chloroquine for 6 months once a day and last few weeks once every other day.  I had bloodwork taken every few weeks and visits to doctor.   My last visit to doctor with bloodwork was on November 9.  He called me with results and it was perfect or at least normal.  My CRP was down to .5.  He told me at that point he was sure the reaction had been caused by the  covid vaccine because he said there is no way everything would have resolved in 6 months on the Chloroquine if it was anything else.  I had an autoimmune reaction to the covid vaccine causing the heart issues.  I was also sent for a heart MRI  on May 10 and had extreme biatrial enlargement.
LAB_DATA: Tests and laboratory results during hospital stay April 1, 2021-April 7, 2021.   Several Chest X-ray, CT head scan, C-T Scan Chest, CTA abdomen,  Carotid Doppler Bilateral, Swabs for several infectious diseases - all negative, Autoimmune Studies, several Echocardiograms, constant bloodwork, urine tests, several Covid swabs -  all negative.   All records for these tests can be found at hospital, hospitalization April 1- April 7, 2021.  It's too much to include on this form.  More bloodwork was done on outpatient basis after leaving the hospital.  Heart MRI at Hospital on May 10, 2021.  Appt. with doctor on May 13, 2021 with breathing tests.  Doctor on May 18, 2021.  He took 13 vials of blood to test and put me on Chloroquine.    Met with doctor, Electrophysiology and Cardiology on June 8, 2021.  Met with doctor on September 13, 2021 where he did more bloodwork.  He continued me on Chloroquine.  I had an Echocardiogram on October 8, 2021.  Met with my Cardiologist on October 18, 2021.  Met with doctor on November 8, 2021 for more breathing tests.  Met with doctor on November 9, 2021.  He did more bloodwork which  came back normal and he took me off Chloroquine at that time.  He concluded I had an autoimmune reaction to the vaccine because nothing else would have resolved itself in 6 months with the Chloroquine had it been anything else.
OTHER_MEDS: Benicar HCt 20/12.5 mg,, Bupropian 75 mg/2 times per day, next Multi vitamin, calcium, D3 2000 IU

SYMPTOM_TEXT: No immediate symptoms other than a sore arm at injection site that lasted for about 24 hours.  At approximately 36 hours I  noticed a ringing in my ears and blurred vision with pressure behind my left eye.  Went to eye doctor for the second time this year and she could find no abnormalities other than more floaters, which is consistent for my age.  Went to Audiologist to have my hearing tested.   Confirmed it was tinnitus and during hearing test the audiologist had to "pulse" the tones so I could hear them.  Tinnitus is in both ears, sounds like a white noise machine and has not subsided 8 months later.  Went to my MD in October and she suggested I report my symptoms, but I didn't at the time.  She recommended a brain MRI, which did not show anything significant, but since the vision issue has not subsided the radiologist suggested an MRI of the optic nerve, which is scheduled for mid January 2022.  She also referred me to a neurologist and the first available appointment is also mid January 2022.  Saw the NP at the clinic today and she also suggested I submit my symptoms and I will follow up at the clinic after the eye MRI and the neurologist appointment.  Tinnitus is getting louder.
LAB_DATA: Audiologist - August 17, 2021 Brain MRI - November 8, 2021 Optic Nerve MRI scheduled for January 10, 2022 Neurologist scheduled for January 7, 2022

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my Moderna booster shot on 11/24/21.  In the early morning hours of 12/10/2021, I woke up with full body hives. They were everywhere but my face, bottoms of feet and palms of hands. I took Benadryl and Zyrtex for 24 hours and the hives were still severe. Next, I had a medical visit on 12/11/2021, and they prescribed me Prednisone. I took it for four days with Zyrtec. I did this regimine until Wednesday 12/15.  The steroid was not working, so I went to get a Strep test.  Strep was negative.  I finally, got a primary care provider visit on Friday, 12/17 at 11:30 AM.  She told me to do the following; Zyrtec (two pills in the AM and two in the PM), Pepcid twice daily (Famotidine 15 mg tablet), Hydroxyzine 25 mg tablet up to 3 times per day for itching. ( I also will continue my Citilopram (40 mg. 1x per day). The itching subsided over the next 24 hours, but I decided to add in a histamine low diet.  This is where I noticed the most improvements. I still have full body hives, they flare up in the middle of the night or when I am hot, but they are more flat during the day and less itchy. I can go back to work (unless I get a flare-- then I cannot concentrate and have to sit in a cold bath). I am on day 10 of hives.
LAB_DATA: I have not had any lab tests.  (Except a strep test that was negative).  I also took an at home covid test the evening of 12/11/21, which was negative.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client was 12 years old on the date of vaccination, and received the Pfizer formulation for ages 5-11. Both vaccine types were offered at this clinic. Multiple safeguards to prevent this type of error were in place, including color-coded wristbands, staff education prior to the clinic and just-in-time training at clinic, only one vaccine type per vaccinator station, and at least 2 points in clinic flow where age and vaccine type are verified. This error was discovered after the clinic during record review. The client's guardian (mother) was informed. She misinterpreted the posted signage and thought there was only one type of vaccine available for children <18 years old, and brought this client and their younger sibling to the same table. The vaccinator did not verify age before administering. Per CDC guidance, the client may receive another age-appropriate dose of Pfizer vaccine in 21 days; this was discussed with the client's guardian. At the time of this submission, no known adverse effects have occurred.
Patient was given an expired Moderna vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: covid vaccine breakthrough

1st shot 3/23/21 I began experiencing what I believed to be heartburn I had never before in my life experienced heartburn and started feeling that within a week 3/26/21 of receiving the shot. I started over-the-counter meds such as Prevacid, Tums, Pepto Bismol and nothing helped. 3 weeks later I went to my primary care doctor for treatment where I was prescribed omeprazole and later on Prilosec first on a dosage of 20mg then a dosage of 40mg. The medication didn't help and only seemed to make it worse.  I was referred to a gastroenterologist in May 2021 and was not able to see my doctor until June 2021. At the time I received the second shot where I began to have ear-burning pain and numbness sensation in my face. I was having numbness around my nostrils, mouth, and cheeks. The ear burning would feel like it's inside my ear canal. My primary care doctor saw no issue in my ears but suggested a gastroenterologist anyway. My gastro suggested I do an endoscopy with bravo and the findings stated I was not having sufficient acid reflux to have the symptoms I was having. Especially the ear burning, he suggested that could be an allergy but did not order an allergy test and I was advised to see an ENT instead. My ENT did an allergy test which came back negative. My ENT also did a barium swallow to confirm no heartburn and everything was negative and I am still having ear-burning pain, minty /hot throat. It is debilitating and painful where it disrupts my way of life constantly.  I currently have no treatment and am dealing with this every day.   My ENT has suggested TMJ as the cause but I had never had any jaw issues in my life up until receiving the vaccine. He is also not 100% sure as some of my symptoms do not line up with the TMJ symptoms. I am still trying to get a diagnosis 6-7 months later. I have also had my upper wisdom teeth removed to see if the pressure of my wisdom teeth was causing this but 2 weeks post wisdom teeth removal I am still facing the same symptoms.
LAB_DATA: Endoscopy with Bravo- June 2021 Allergy Test September 2021 Barium Swallow October 2021 MRI December 2021
OTHER_MEDS: Omeprazole, Prilosec medication was started within a week of first vaccination on 3/23/2021. Started to have what felt like heartburn shortly after the first shot. Primary care doctor prescribed medications for it.
HISTORY: Currently my ENT states I have developed TMJ I have been experiencing these effects since my second shot of the vaccine

On the day of the vaccine I experienced extreme muscle spasms including a clenching jaw and stomach spasms. My stomach felt like it was being grabbed and squeezed and turned around in my body. This lasted approximately one to two weeks. I was also unable to eat without nausea and indigestion (which I had never experienced before) and began experiencing EXTREME bloating and severe abdominal pain. I went to Emergency Room on April 22 - two weeks after receiving the vaccine due to above listed symptoms. A CT scan revealed no blockages. They gave me antacids and morphine, neither of which reduced the pain or nausea. I saw a GI Specialist Dr. on April 27 who thought it might be an ulcer and prescribed me medication that made me feel worse. I discontinued the medication and saw Dr., another GI Specialist, who performed endoscopy and Colonscopy. I have the reports from that procedure which note inflammation/gastritis and no evidence of chronic illness (because I have no history of GI Issues and was healthy until the vaccine). Dr. diagnosed me with SIBO, gave me some antibiotics and referred me to a nutritionist. My symptoms continued to worsen and my hair started falling out. I am now being treated by Dr. from Nutrition Dept. It has been nearly a year and I am still disabled. I experience extreme bloating which prevents me from moving or eating and I cannot eat very many foods. I cannot work and have had to drop out of school. Please contact me and let me know what could be causing these symptoms. I am pro-vaccine but I've had an adverse reaction and deserve help understanding and navigating my response so that I can heal. In addition, these vaccines must be made safe for everyone and understanding adverse outcomes is crucial to that.
LAB_DATA: CT Scan from Emergency Room on 4/22/21; Endoscopy and Colonscopy from Dr. on 5/25/21; I have an appointment with a specialist on 2/22/22 who will perform more tests. Some specialists have long waiting lists.

Experienced a severe allergic reaction 3 days after my second dose of the Pfizer vaccine.  It happened after eating dinner a restaurant.  At the time I was 29 years old and had never experienced any type of food allergy (mild or severe).  I experienced hives and redness all over my body including my face and neck.  I was treated with prednisone and Benadryl.  The symptoms faded an hour after taking medication.  The reaction did not cause any airway problems.  Additionally I had a similar allergic reaction 30 days later after eating breakfast.  This time benadryl was the only drug available and symptoms also faded afterwards.  Obviously one could assume this is a coincidence.  Six months have now passed and I have not had any further allergic reactions.  So in my 30 years living I have had only 2 reactions. And both were 3 days and 30 days following Pfizer vaccine.  All of the foods I ate during the 2 meals which caused the reaction were not new to me.  I had eaten them before with no reaction.  I thought I should share this with your database.
LAB_DATA: I have now been tested using skin and blood tests for many allergies.  On October 12, 2021 it was confirmed I am allergic to chicken, green peas, gluten and pollen.  I previously frequently ate chicken and gluten.

We explained to the mother what had happened and apologized extensively. We reassured her that this has happened elsewhere before, and no major adverse outcomes have occurred. Discussed that, if anything, she may have a stronger immune response, including increased redness and swelling in the area, as well as systemic symptoms such as fever, chills, fatigue. Counseled mother than she can use tylenol and ibuprofen as needed, and that if she has any further concerns, she should not hesitate to call or bring her back in for evaluation. Also discussed that she will need to get the booster dose at the pediatric clinic, as they currently have the child dose of the vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: In April, I had liquid diarrhea and it was pretty much liquid diarrhea for 8 weeks. I couldn't eat anything, and I had to have a specific diet with bananas, rice, applesauce and toast, plenty of fluids and water. That's all I ate for those weeks. The doctor put me on 6 Pepto Bismol tablets. He didn't want to give me any severe things in the end. It was about 8 weeks and I had lost 14 pounds during this time. I also felt very nauseated at night. I never vomited or anything and it was all bowel related. And it was probably inflammation in that area. Food would go straight through me. I had stomach cramps and pain in the back. I was very weak and tired, and I wasn't eating much and losing weight and very fatigued. My doctor said it was colitis over the telehealth. I did go in for a test and a stool sample done at the local clinic and I had bacteria and they diagnosed with colitis. Two stool sample tests that confirmed colitis. 1st test looked for C-diff and colitis. The 2nd one confirmed that it was colitis. Since then, I've been doing okay.
LAB_DATA: 1st stool sample indicated colitis. 2nd stool sample indicated colitis

In brief, patient is a previously healthy 15 year old who had acute headache and collapse at home, concern for posturing versus seizure, and ultimately found to have cerebral and intraventricular hemorrhage with mass effect secondary to ruptured aneurysm. S/p coiling of aneurysm, bilateral EVD placement and R decompressive craniectomy. She has acute respiratory failure, strep viridans bacteremia, and concurrent COVID-19 infection.  Presented 12/2/21 with aneurysm and incidentally found to be COVID positive.   NEURO: On arrival, she was somewhat responsive and by the time she arrived at ED she was posturing versus seizing. Head CT revealed hemorrhage 3x3x3 hemorrhagic focus anterior and inferior to the right basal ganglion with mass effect, also with intraventricular blood in lateral and third ventricles with acute subarachnoid hemorrhage in suprasellar cistern and bilateral sylvian fissures. At that time, reportedly pupils equal, 3-4, minimally reactive. At ED, received Mannitol bolus, and 4mg Ativan administered. Flight for Life activated and upon arrival to CW was admitted to the PICU with plan for emergent EVD placement. Neurosurgery placed EVD at bedside. Repeat head CT and CTA performed and demonstrated bilobed aneurysm arising from right ICA terminus with enlarging intraparenchymal hematoma along superior aspect mostly likely representing a ruptured aneurysm, increased intraventricular hemorrhage, similar subarachnoid hemorrhage, increased mass effect, effacement of basal cisterns, worsened midline shift. Optimized neuroprotection management with sedation, neuromuscular blockade, ventilator management, and hypertonic saline. R pupil became dilated and nonreactive and patient demonstrated persistently elevated ICPs >50. She underwent emergent IR coiling and R decompressive craniectomy with second right-sided EVD placement. Patient continued to demonstrate ICPs in 20s. Worked with Neurosurgery to optimize sedation. Repeat head CT demonstrated increased hypoattenuation in right frontal and parietal lobes, left parietal lobe, and splenium of corpus callosum. Loss of gray-white differentiation concerning for ischemic change. Increased right to left midline shift. TCDs demonstrated moderate spasm of the L MCA. EEG without seizure. Started Pentobarbital coma. On 12/9, an occurred episode while in transport to MRI and patient was noted to be obtunded. ICP 11 during episode, EVDs patent. She was not connected to LTM during episode, as she was in transport. She was started on epi drip and became more responsive, moving spontaneously and withdrawing to pain. On 12/10, her neurostorming medication regimen was optimized and no further changes were made.    Given poor neurologic prognosis, patient was given adequate sedation for pain management during terminal extubation on 12/18.  CV: Had periods of hypotension intraoperatively requiring initiation of Epinephrine and Norepinephrine infusions to maintain goal MAP > 80, SBP > 120. Returned to PICU with femoral CVL, arterial line, sedated with Fentanyl and Dexmedetomidine infusions, and on Vecuronium infusions, Nimodipine. On 12/4 echocardiogram report noted significant for left ventricular mid-inferoseptal hypokinesis and moderately diminished left ventricular systolic function, with an LVEF 41%. She required titration of pressors to maintain goal pressures. Added stress dose Hydrocortisone. Repeat echocardiogram demonstrated significant improvement in LV systolic function, consistent with the hypothesis that myocardium was neurologically stunned. 12/6-12/8 Patient weaned from sedation and pressors. On 12/9 she experienced a hypotensive episode while in transport to MRI.  HR dropped to 40s-50s. 105 mcg Epi dwindle given, then started on Epi drip, given 500 mL NS push pull. HR and BP normalized. On 12/10, patient was weaned from pressors and stress dose steroids. She remained hemodynamically appropriate leading to terminal extubation on 12/18.   RESP: Intubated in the OR. Notably, course complicated by significant pulmonary edema with poor compliance. On 12/10, her ventilator settings were weaned to CPAP/PS. She remained hemodynamically appropriate with CPAP/PS until terminal extubation on 12/18.   FEN/GI: On 12/10 patient was started on enteral feeds which were discontinued after terminal extubation on 12/18.   ID: At ED, she was incidentally found to be COVID positive. Blood cultures were drawn at that time positive for strep viridans. She started on empiric Cefepime and Vancomycin due to concern for septic shock given pressor requirements. Initiated thermoregulation. Patient continued to be intermittently febrile and remained on Ceftriaxone per family's wishes until 12/19.   RENAL: Initially had significantly increased urine output. Labs concerning for DI, although could also be secondary to 3% boluses. Initiated DI protocol. This later resolved and she continued to have urine output appropriate for age leading to her terminal extubation on 12/18.   OTHER: On 12/5 ,discussion took place between provider and mother and placed partial code status, including no bolus cardiac resuscitative medications, no defibrillation, no chest compressions. Care Conference took place on 12/10, during which mother voiced she would like to get MRI for further neuroprognostication before changing goals of care. Care conference on 12/14 to discuss MRI results with family. Neurology explained likely deficits patient will experience as a result of her brain injury including weakness of both sides of her body, inability to walk, inability to effectively eat PO, personality changes, cognitive dysfunction. Mother voices "Patient would not want to live like this," but requests time to discuss these options with family before making any decisions. Another discussion between providers and family on 12/15 during which family voiced they would not want patient to be reintubated once extubated, would not want her to receive blood products, and would like to continue with enteral feeding. Tentative plans for extubation on 12/17 or 12/18 once family from out of state has come to say their goodbyes. Family later decided to move forward with terminal extubation on 12/18. She was extubated 12/18 to room air and passed away on 12/19/2021 @ 20:37 PM with mother, brother and step father at the bedside.
LAB_DATA: Head CT, MRI, Echocardiogram, multiple ultrasounds, angiogram

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Had fever, chills, body aches (similar to Pfizer first and second dose) for 48 hours. However, those are not the reasons for this report... the primary reason for this report is that I had extreme pain at the site of injection within hours of receiving the injection. The intense stabbing pain was so severe I could not move my arm for days. The pain would wake me at night. The pain would not go down to a zero in any position although Advil helped me go to sleep, but I could only sleep flat on my back.  Once the pain began to subside and movement was available to me (12/11/21) I realized there was also significant weakness (particularly with abduction and flexion).  Passive range of motion was available with painful end feels at near end of range; however, active range against gravity was not possible. While my arm has been very slowly improving I still have a dull nearly constant pain, significant weakness, and continue to be very limited in my activities of daily living. Treatment has included Advil as needed (primarily for sleep and during the first 2-3 days following injection) and active assisted range of motion in all planes within a painfree range using a warm bath with epsom salt for about 1 hour about 4-5x/week.

I received a tingling sensation on my left arm immediately following the injection. Then over the next 24 hours I experienced soreness at the injection point, a headache, and fatigue. These symptoms went away and then about mid-next week (18 Aug 21) I started to experience chest tightening at rest and more intensely if I was walking or doing anything that was mildly physical. I Initially thought this was a panic attack (which was strange because I had never experienced a panic attack in my life). The chest tightening symptoms ebbed and flowed for about two weeks and eventually subsided. I also started to experienced black dots floating in my peripheral vision (these still have not gone away but appear sporadically). This was also strange because i never experienced this in my life.
LAB_DATA: When the chest tightening continued went to the doctor and they sent me away. Then, I went to another doctor and they administered an EKG, troponin blood test, and an ultra sound of the heart. The doctor said while there may be soft/mild cardiac inflammation it is not to a severe enough degree to appear on the test. The doctor he has found a number of patients who have had these side effects to the COVID-19 vaccine with these same symptoms. He said they typically recover in several weeks with rest. He told me not to do any intense physical activity until my symptoms cleared and then after my symptoms cleared I could resume intense physical activity (such as running or working out) again. I began to recover (but still had some symptoms) before I received the second dose of the vaccine on October 15, 2021 which produced chest tightening symptoms again as well as continued black dots floating in my peripheral vision. My decision to receive the vaccine was entirely due to a mandate with the threat of termination of employment for non-compliance.

Over the following 2-3 months, more of my Hashimoto's symptoms flared up in addition to the chills and headaches -- sudden weight loss, fatigue, hair loss, constipation, dry flaky skin, excessive sense of cold even on hot days in summer, splitting nails.  Now in December 2021, the headaches and chills have calmed somewhat and are less severe but still present, and all other symptoms are ongoing.  I had 3 PCR covid tests in late May 2021 and all were negative. I have not been to see a doctor about this yet because I'm new to the area and don't have a specialist yet locally.  I'm very reluctant to have the covid booster, as I fear it will worsen the Hashimoto's symptoms that are finally improving after over 7 months of dealing with the reaction the last time.

After my daughter received her second shot on 10/10/2021 she woke up around midnight and stated that it hurt to breathe.  So we had her take a shower, take some Tylenol and take a nebulizer treatment to try help her lungs open up.  After doing this it didn't help but she was able to fall back to sleep on and off. I did take her to the ER the next day because her pediatrician stated to go there.  When we got the ER which after only 45 minutes then sent us home and said it was nothing to worry about.  She wasn't getting any better so on 10/12/2021 I brought her to the walk in clinic for hospital for a second option. They stated that they couldn't read what ever ER wrote for the EKG so they were going back and forth with the ER's trying to figure out what we should do.  After listening to her and trying to read the EKG they had thought that the wall of the heart was was swollen and said we could go home but they made an appointment for her to see a Cardiologist at Hospital.  When we saw MD, he also stated that he couldn't read ER's EKG so he would have to do another one.  After reading the EKG that he ran he did state that he did believe that the wall around he heart was swollen.  He stated that it is a rare case that it happens in girls because they have been seeing it more in boys.  He also said that it should heal on it's own but could take a few weeks to a month to heal.  After about 3 weeks it did seem to go away but about once a week to every other week she will get some pains and says it is hard to breathe again.   This will last a few minutes to a few hours and then goes away.
LAB_DATA: 2 EKG's done (in 2 different hospitals on different days)

Patient reports adverse effect Johnson & Johnson COVID-19 vaccine that she received on November 22, 2021.  This vaccine was given because she had a previous adverse reaction to the Pfizer mRNA vaccine which was a bit more suspicious for an immediate hypersensitivity type reaction and so based on the CDC guidelines and allergy practice recommendations we discussed the risks and benefits of receiving the Johnson & Johnson COVID-19 vaccine and she wanted to proceed with this vaccination.    She reports pain immediately upon receiving the injection that resolved within 5 minutes or so.  She felt a little "off" at work for the remaining of the workday.  She felt like her jaw was sort of tight but otherwise cannot identify any specific problems.   In the car in the way home her friend noted that she had hive-like rash at her face and she also relates that she had hive like a rash at her chest and arms.  This was not pruritic however. This waxed and waned for a few hours and then was completely gone by the next day.  Upon returning home she also began to experience body aches.  Tried to have some dinner and immediately felt nausea.  She began vomiting around 6:30 PM and vomited multiple times until she feels as though there is nothing left to vomit.  She tried taking omeprazole and immediately vomited that up.  She was gagging and vomiting.  She also then began having diarrhea and later on in the evening and continued with intermittent vomiting anytime she would try to eat and loose stools for the rest of that week.  On day 3 of symptoms she began using Pedialyte and was able to hold down Pedialyte in small amounts.  By Saturday, so day 5 after her shot she began to feel essentially normal.  She is still experiencing intermittent nausea.  She lost 5 pounds.  She did not experience additional rash.  Did not experience swelling, difficulty breathing, cough, wheeze.  Prior to the vaccine she had taken 10 mg of loratadine and 1000 mg of acetaminophen.  She had to remain home from work for the rest of that week.
HISTORY: Migraine Constipation GERD Allergic rhinitis Food allergy s/p gastric bypass surgery
PRIOR_VAX: Pfizer mRNA COVID19 vaccine
ALLERGIES: Peanut Promethazine Simvastatin Pfizer mRNA COVID19 vaccine

I got the 1st dose Pfizer vaccine on 11/11. I had normal headache and tiredness 24 hr post vaccine. I developed minor cold symptoms later that week. On 11/20, I was laying down in bed at night watching a movie and felt slightly congested so I used some Flonase. 30 min later I got a weird head rush feeling, felt jittery and hot, hands and feet had some tingling, heart palpitations/racing. Originally I thought maybe these symptoms were attributed to the Flonase. The episode took about 2 hr to calm down enough to fall finally lay down and relax/fall asleep. The next day on 11/21 that night I had the same symptoms of feeling weird and heart palpitations. Since the initial start of these symptoms I was having intermittent episodes of heart palpitations, chest tightness, feeling like I can't take a deep breath, headaches, and random tingling sensations in my left shoulder blade. I went to the ER for these symptoms because I was woken up out of sleep feeling like my heart skipped a beat and needing to gasp for a breath and then followed with a really fast HR (low 100s - my baseline HR was normally in upper 50s to lower 60s) , cardiac workup was normal at that time but got referred to cardiology. I am currently wearing a Holter monitor. I had these symptoms for a total duration of 3 weeks. The symptoms started to subside/improve last Tuesday on 12/14. I am still waiting on results from the Holter monitor.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: PMH:  CHF, TAVR, HTN, MDD, peripheral neuropathy; admitted to hosp with c/o SOB, cough, lethargy; positive for COVID; started on dexamethasone, redesivir; O2 supplementation, BiPAP; increased work of breathing; condition continued to deteriorate; moved to comfort measures; pt died in the hosp

After 4 days of severe symptoms to the Pfizer Covid-19 booster shot (102 fever for almost 36 hours, beyond painful body aches, nausea, headaches, cognitive issues, chills, etc.), I was feeling better, just tired from mounting such a large immune response and then 2 days later, I woke up with loud ringing and reverberation all over my entire head and could not hear. Upon getting up, I realized it was only my right ear that had the ringing, tinnitus, underwater muffled head pounding and complete hearing loss. I went to my PCP that day who confirmed it was not a blockage or infection and gave me 125 mg steroid shot immediately to calm the immune/inflammatory reaction. She referred me to an ENT specialist who I saw the next day, on December 9th, who has seen this unfortunate reaction in all three doses of the Covid-19 vaccine. He checked my hearing to confirm the difference between the ears and total loss in the right ear. I was prescribed high dose oral Prednisone for 17 days and have still seen no results at all. I still have complete unilateral hearing loss and bad tinnitus and discomfort in my right side of the head, I can barely function. It is unclear if this will improve or if I will get any of my hearing back. I am not against vaccines at all, but this tragic and I am NOT the only person who has had this experience, pleaae do more research and share more information with the public about this. A vaccine should not be able to take away someone's hearing.
LAB_DATA: Hearing test by audiologist on 12/9/21 - above average hearing in left ear, none in right ear.

I was just sitting at the dinner table, and I went to go scratch and on my collar bone on the left side. When I touched the collar bone area, it hurt. There was a little bump in that area. I took my finger and palpated through that area to see what it was and what I was feeling. I also had my boyfriend feel it as well. It might have been a little larger than a pea size. I definitely felt something that I had not felt before. It was sensitive to the touch. I waited a day but then I did make an appointment to go to the doctor to have it checked. I didn't think it had anything to do with the vaccine at the time, but I wasn't sure if it was something different. They did feel around and felt something, so they sent me for an ultrasound. They said it was in the area of the thyroid and they did the ultrasound. They said that if I felt anything larger or hurting more while waiting for my results, (my doctor also asked if I had received my vaccine, on the left side) she had read that there were cases of enlargement of the thyroid on the side of where the vaccine was given. They called me a few days later and let me know that there was nothing wrong. They said if anything changed to come back in. The doctor said in a couple months to come back in if it got worst. After about that time, I didn't feel anything anymore and they never did another ultrasound. And I have not felt anything since then.

12/8 Received first Pfizer vaccines. Had some arm pain after but otherwise felt well. 12/9 early AM, woke up with palpitations (felt heart throughout his body). HR was 92 and BP 130/93. 2-3 more similar episodes that morning and early afternoon. That morning, also developed non-exertional, non-positional L chest pain. Quality- mild and stabbing. Some lateral radiation. Will last a few minutes and then resolve. Occurs several times per day. Has gradually become less bothersome. No associate dyspnea, lightheadedness, leg swelling, PND, or orthopnea. Also developed mild but persistent chest tightness. Has had intermittent tremors throughout body, more vibratory sensation than visible tremor. Keeping him from sleep. ROS+ for 12 hours of sleep for the first 2 nights after vaccine  12/13 - Presented to clinic for evaluation. Continues to have intermittent chest pain, vibratory sensation, chest tightness, and fatigue. Chest pain may be more infrequent. Chest tightness has improved. Palpitations and sensation of skipped heartbeats have resolved. No fevers, headache, or vision changes.  Started on Aleve and tizanidine qhs prn (pt did not trial).  12/17- Seen at clinic for follow-up. Continued symptom improvement but persistent tremors. HR 108. Recommend increasing to Aleve 440mg BID for 1-2 week trial and tizanidine qHS for tremors.

Patient sat down next to me on the couch around 4:00 PM Dec 7 (Tuesday). I was finishing work (I work in clinical drug development) and he sat back on the couch. His head went back onto the cushion and tilted to the right side. His eyes rolled into his head, he started mumbling incoherent words, and was unresponsive to me calling his name several times. The event lasted several seconds (maybe 5-6 seconds in total) at which he was unresponsive/lost consciousness. It seems that he either had a seizure or experienced some sort of syncope. He then came to, and had absolutely no recollection that any event had taken place. No realization at all. Had I not witnessed the event, neither one of us would have known that anything untoward had occurred. After the event he was extremely tired and slept for about an hour or so. He had a visit scheduled with his rheumatologist for December 9 (2 days post-event) where he mentioned this event. His Rheumatologist recommended that he report the event to VAERS as this seizure/syncope occurred within ~72 hours post-vaccination (3rd shot, booster, Pfizer COVID-19). Patient has had no other known events since that initial adverse event.

I felt like I had flu, so I stayed home and slept. I had a bad headache and a low-grade fever at about 99 degrees. I don't have a rash, but I feel like I'm going to break out in one. I went to bed early on Saturday night. I woke the next morning and felt a little better. I felt like I had another fever. I took aspirin. I had gone out then came home and felt sick again. I was tired, felt like I had flu, and I had massive body aches.  On Friday after 1st hour everything was getting inflamed. On Sunday the inflammation went down. Today I still have pretty bad body pain. My muscles are very tightened up. I still have the hive feeling. I got a fever again. I took temp and it was 99 degrees. I feel flushed and tired. The hive feeling came back mainly on left side. My arm on Friday started to swell up, bruised, sore, and puffy. Tonight, I took an aspirin and an antihistamine. My tongue feels like it is going to break out in a rash too. I didn't do anything all weekend. I had COVID back in March 2020. I have only been prescribed Benadryl.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Chest pain and spasms 14hrs after vaccination, went to ER, diagnoses with PVCs, which I never had before the shot. Over the next week my ears, especially the left, began to feel full. Significant tinnitus noticed a week later along with hearing loss. Went to an ENT and hearing test showed hearing loss at high frequencies. Prednisone, and then nortriptyline was prescribed. Little to no improvement six months later. Several weeks after the shot experienced extreme dermatitis, even on hands and was unable to wear my 18k wedding rings. My jeweler dipped them in 24k gold, and without me telling him about the vaccine, he said that something in my body must be reacting to the metal. Citrus fruits and tomatoes also seemed to trigger rashes. Around this time I also began to experience pins and needles/neuropathy like symptoms, and some limb weakness. I also experienced the worst seasonal allergies after the shot and never had them before. Prior to the shot I was seropositive for COVID antibodies. Since the shot I have not felt the same and was previously fit and healthy. The adverse reactions have decreased my quality of life.

LAB_DATA: Prescription Medications -- Tested for UTI in July 2021 came up negative, but the infection cleared up with Macrobid.  Ten days after Macrobid, I developed a bad case of hives and was treated with prescription antihistamine and anti-inflammatory.  November 28, 2021 -- my dermatologist conducted a telehealth visit by phone after I sent photographs of the Shingles. She ordered Valtrex, Keflex, Mucipricin and several OTC topical ointments/antiseptic soaks which helped.  I then saw her in person for a visit on December 17 as they had still not resolved.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 2 days after my 2nd dose, I started feeling really tired and had a dry cough and that progressed, and I started getting pressure in my lung area, so I got more concerned because my cough got worse. I went into my doctor's office and when she listened to my lungs, she could hear a wheeze. She sent me for lung x-ray, but it didn't come back that I had pneumonia and they didn't think it was COVID at that time, but my breathing got harder and harder, and the wheeze got more and more. I was just on albuterol at first, but within 2 weeks after doctor's appointment, they called me back in because it was harder to breathe. I got another lung x-ray, but it looked the same, and they called it bronchitis and could see irritation. They put me on Budesonide and Albuterol, and it was like that for another 6 weeks and I had to increase it and had to use a nebulizer and I started using both formulas and that took about 4 weeks doing 4x a day. I went to pulmonologist at that point, and she took me off Albuterol and put me on Symbicort 2 puffs 2x a day and I'm still on that and I'm breathing a lot better, and my lungs look better but there is still irritation. It's still ongoing but it's not as bad. It's under control and I am coughing up gooey yucky stuff from my lungs and I am doing that when I wake up and I've never been a smoker. I do have a history of asthma, but I haven't had any episodes of it in 5 years until the vaccine. There was also crushing fatigue and days that I would get out of bed, and I just couldn't seem to do anything and the brain fog and absolute exhaustion and that could be that I wasn't getting a lot of oxygen and that lasted until about a month ago and little by little it has gotten better.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 58 y/o woman with obesity with BMI of 34, HTN, T2DM (A1c: 6.6%), HLD, vaccinated against COVID x2 (no booster), who presented to the ED on 12/13 with fever, dizziness, cough and nausea, vomiting found to have covid pneumonia with acute hypoxemic respiratory failure.    Hospital course:    COVID Pneumonia with acute hypoxemic Respiratory failure: Symptom onset on 12/6, COVID positive on 12/13. Last fever on 12/12. There was a documentation of O2 sat of 88% during sleep in ED so she was started on steroids and remdesivir and HBS was consulted. However, she has remained 96-97% at rest and 95% on exertion. Her fatigue and dizziness has resolved. She received 3 days of decadron and remdesivir. Given she has no hypoxemia and decadron worsened her blood glucose levels, will not Discharge on decadron. Her liver enzymes remains within normal limit. CRP trending down. She was on lovenox for DVT PPx. She will be discharged with covid kit. Booster within a month when feeling better. Patient discharged after (9) day inpatient admission. Patient is a 79-year-old female with history of hyperlipidemia who presented to the ED on 12/08 with complaints of cough and shortness of breath.  He was seen at urgent care several days prior to presentation, diagnosed with COVID, and placed on Tessalon Perles with discharge home.  Upon presentation to the emergency department, he was hypotensive with a blood pressure of 88/59.  He was hypoxemic, and placed on 100% non-rebreather mask.  EKG showed sinus bradycardia with a right bundle branch block and left anterior fascicular block.  Chest x-ray showed pneumonia, consistent with COVID.  Due to his low blood pressure readings, he was given a 500 mL bolus of normal saline.  Due to concerns for superimposed bacterial infection, he was given IV Rocephin and azithromycin, as well as IV Decadron, and admitted to the hospitalist service for further management.   Upon admission, he was transitioned to high-flow nasal cannula oxygen.  Decadron, Rocephin and azithromycin were continued.  He was switched from non-rebreather to high-flow nasal cannula oxygen for admission.  He was started on Remdesivir, but this was stopped secondary to bradycardia.  Due to the severity of his bradycardia, cardiology was consulted.  They recommended continuing telemetry monitoring, and placed a 14-day Zio patch at discharge, and to avoid AV nodal blocking agents.   He had a rather significant increase in D-dimer by 12/13, so CTA thorax and bilateral lower extremity venous Doppler were obtained.  He was noted to have small bilateral pulmonary emboli as well as nonocclusive, mobile thrombus in the right common femoral vein.  He was placed on Lovenox 1 mg/kg twice daily.  This was later transitioned to Eliquis 10 mg twice daily.  He will continue on Eliquis 10 mg twice daily at discharge, with decreased to 5 mg twice daily after 7 days.  He has 10 you on Eliquis for at least 6 months of therapy.   During hospitalization, we were able to gradually wean his oxygen down.  He was able to discharge on room air.   He was felt stable for discharge home on 12/17/2021.  He will discharge home on Eliquis 10 mg twice daily for 4 more days, and then decrease to 5 mg twice daily.  He will be placed on a prednisone taper beginning at 30 mg, and decreasing by 10 mg every 3 days.  14-day Zio patch will be placed at discharge as well to evaluate for bradycardia.  He should follow-up with his PCP in 1 week.

swollen face; swollen tongue; rare allergic reaction; itchy; rashes on her entire torso / legs, back, neck and hands / stomach and forearms; throat closed; could not swallow; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of allergic reaction in a 55-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   Co-suspect products included prednisone unknown for product used for unknown indication.   On 17th November 2021 11:00, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix. On 18th November 2021, the patient started prednisone 40 mg at an unknown frequency. On an unknown date, the dose was changed to 20 mg at an unknown frequency. On 9th October 2021, the dose was changed to 10 mg at an unknown frequency. On 17th November 2021, less than an hour after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced allergic reaction, pruritus, generalized rash, throat constriction and unable to swallow. On 21st November 2021, the patient experienced facial swelling and swollen tongue. The patient was treated with benadryl (nos) (Benadryl) and steroids nos (Steroid (Not Specified)). The action taken with prednisone was unknown. On an unknown date, the outcome of the allergic reaction, throat constriction, unable to swallow, facial swelling and swollen tongue were unknown and the outcome of the pruritus was recovered/resolved and the outcome of the generalized rash was not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the allergic reaction, pruritus, generalized rash, throat constriction, unable to swallow, facial swelling and swollen tongue to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: This case was reported by the patient herself. The patient received the first dose of Shingrix and within an hour, she started feeling itchy.  Four hours after she received the vaccine she was covered in rashes on her entire torso. Rash was also seen on her legs, back, neck and hands.  Later that night, her throat closed and she could not swallow.  She stated that she went to the emergency room in the morning of 18th November 2021 where she was given 40 mg prednisone.  3 days later, she experienced a swollen face and swollen tongue.  Her doctor gave her a large dose of steroid (name unknown).  She had been taking 20 mg prednisone for the last week and she took 10mg prednisone yesterday.  She had also been using Benadryl on her rashes to help treat it.  She was still experiencing rash which was seen on her stomach and forearms.  The patient also had a rare allergic reaction. Emergency room visit was required. It was unknown if the reporter considered the allergic reaction, pruritus, generalized rash, throat constriction, unable to swallow, facial swelling and swollen tongue to be related to Prednisone. The patient was previously vaccinated with covid-19 vaccine ad26. cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 1802068, expiry: 23-AUG-2021) dose was not reported, 01 total was administered on 23-MAR-2021 on left arm for prophylactic vaccination (dose number in series 1). The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 1855194 expiry: 09-APR-2022) dose was not reported, 01 total was administered on 17-NOV-2021 on left arm for prophylactic vaccination (dose number in series 2). On 02-DEC-2021, following vaccination with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (dose number in series 2), the patient had cold like symptoms, little/light cough, feeling cold. On the same day, the patient reported a positive coronavirus disease (COVID)-19 test for himself on self (rapid) test when he retested after he began experiencing loss of smell. SYMPTOM_TEXT: STROKE AFTER RECEIVING JANSSEN COVID-19 VACCINE BOOSTER DOSE; This spontaneous report received from a patient concerned a 43 year old female. Initial information processed with additional information received from reporter on 15-DEC-2021. The patient's height was 177.8 cm, and weight were not reported. The patient's concurrent conditions included: environmental allergy, non alcoholic, birth control, and non smoker, and other pre-existing medical conditions included: The patient had no known medical condition and no known drug allergies. The patient did not have any drug abuse/illicit drug use. The patient did not have any other medical history or relevant pre-existing condition. Patient had no illness at time of vaccination. Patient had no history of similar event. Patient had no history of any allergy to vaccine, drug, or food. Patient had no pre-existing acute illness 30 days prior to vaccination. Patient had no history of hospitalization in last 30days, with cause. Patient had no family history of any disease (relevant to vaccination) or allergy. The patient was not not pregnant or breastfeeding at the time of reporting. The patient did not have COVID-19 infection. The patient experienced flu like symptoms, fever, chills, achiness (Dose number in series 1) when received covid-19 vaccine ad26. cov2. s (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 205A21A, expiry: unknown) dose was not reported, 1 total, administered on 12-APR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination (Dose number in series 1). The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, intramuscular, batch number: 211A21A, expiry: 14-DEC-2021, (Gauge/length of the needle: 23 g, 0.6 mm*25 mm, Temperature 38-41 F)) 0.5 ml, 1 total, administered on 08-Dec-2021;12:00 to right arm for prophylactic vaccination (Dose number in series 2). No issue related to the storage of the vaccine. Concomitant medications included montelukast sodium for allergies, levocetirizine dihydrochloride for allergies, and drospirenone/ethinylestradiol betadex clathrate for birth control.  On 08-DEC-2021, immediately after she received the booster dose, she felt a tingling sensation in her mouth and that her mouth went numb. At that time the nurse practitioner given diphenhydramine hydrochloride (benadryl) and lansoprazole (prevacid) and that afterwards nothing happened. The patient passed the phone to other person to complete her report stating previously that she just had a stroke (Dose number in series 2) and so may not be able to complete the call. Reporter stated that, On 09-DEC-2021, around 09:00 to 10:00 A.M, at work the patient started to feel that her vision went blank, her arm started to tingle, she could not make words and so she went to the health facility. At the hospital, she was given the standard of care including an Chest X-ray, Computerised tomogram head and neck, Echocardiogram, MRI brain (Magnetic resonance imaging) and blood work and then was administered Tissue plasminogen activator (TPA) alteplase. Patient visited the emergency room. Patient was stayed in the hospital for a total of about 24 hours was discharged on 10-DEC-2021 with prescriptions for clopidogrel and lipitor. The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient was recovering from tingling sensation in her mouth/arm started to tingle/face tingled, and stroke after receiving Janssen covid-19 vaccine booster dose This report was serious (Hospitalization Caused / Prolonged). This case, involving the same patient is linked to 20211228737.; Sender's Comments: V0:20211229198-COVID-19 VACCINE AD26.COV2.S-Stroke after receiving Janssen covid-19 vaccine booster dose. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I didn't feel the shot. It didn't feel like an IM shot. I asked the pharmacist if she was sure I got it. She said yes.  I left the pharmacy about 15 minutes later and went to downtown  for a celebratory walk and to look at Christmas decorations. Shortly thereafter I had mucus in my throat and I got that scary feeling of not being able to breathe. I returned to the pharmacy. They gave me Benadryl and water.  After about an hour, I was okay. Now though I'm worried I'm not protected against the Omicron variant. I'm a registered nurse and I worry I want be able to protect myself.
PRIOR_VAX: Not sure. I had a rash.
ALLERGIES: After working and frequently wearing latex gloves for 16 hours, I had a significant rash on my hands. And once I had to stop my car in rush hour traffic  because my throat filled with thick mucus. The windows in my car were down. Pollen?

On 04-Dec-2021,  after starting mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine), the patient experienced CELLULITIS (Cellulitis of my right arm) (seriousness criterion medically significant). Patient went off her immunosuppressant medication when Covid-19 1st hit.  It was reported that patient was injured by the person administering the vaccine. On 04-Dec-2021, patient went to the urgent care center. They diagnosed her with Cellulitis of right arm.  Patient was concerned when she saw the pharmacist gave her daughter the injection, because it looked like he gave it real low in her deltoid. Patient notified him that she was a nurse and told him that it goes 2 finger widths below acromion process. The Pharmacist said 'we don't give injections there. It can cause nerve damage. Patient received the injection subcutaneously, in the back of her arm.  Patient called her Dr office and told them what happened. He said in couple of months, maybe she can get another half dose. One patient noted suicidal ideation after the BNT162b2 mRNA vaccine.; The initial case was missing the following minimum criteria: [unidentifiable patient]. Upon receipt of follow-up information on 07Dec2021, this case now contains all required information to be considered valid. This is a literature report.  The primary aim of this study was to assess the impact of vaccine timing, immunological status, demographics, and concomitant treatments on vaccine immunogenicity in autoimmune rheumatic disease (AIRD) patients treated with RTX (rituximab). Secondary aims were to implement an educational intervention to physicians and patients and assess its effect on timing of COVID-19 vaccination in relation to RTX infusions. Authors performed a prospective single center study to optimize SARSCoV-2 vaccination timing and to assess vaccine immunogenicity in AIRD patients who received RTX at a health care hospital. Authors first educated faculty on the rationale for timing SARS-CoV-2 vaccines 24 weeks post-RTX. Authors measured timing of vaccine administration through telephone survey of patients. Authors then analyzed vaccine immunogenicity in relation to vaccine timing and other clinical and immunologic parameters. Patients were contacted by telephone from March through August of 2021. Study participants were surveyed on recent vaccine administration, and in those who had not yet received a vaccination, whether or not they were intending to obtain a COVID-19 vaccine. Vaccine administration was not part of the study. A patient (no qualifiers provided) received bnt162b2 (Batch/Lot number: unknown) as dose number unknown, single for COVID-19 immunisation. Relevant medical history included: "AIRD" (ongoing). Concomitant medication included: RITUXIMAB taken for AIRD. One patient noted suicidal ideation after the BNT162b2 mRNA vaccine. The patient underwent the following laboratory tests and procedures: antineutrophil cytoplasmic antibody: unknown results; blood immunoglobulin G (normal high range 700): unknown results; serum IgM (normal high range 40): unknown results; absolute CD19: unknown results; CD20: unknown results; antinucleocapsid antibody: unknown results; serum IgG antibody levels against SARS-CoV-2: unknown results; SARS-CoV-2 PCR: unknown results. The outcome of the event was unknown.   No follow-up attempts are possible; information about lot/batch number cannot be obtained. No further information is expected.; Sender's Comments: Based on the temporal relationship, the association between the event suicidal ideation with BNT162b2 can not be fully excluded.
